and it tends to be it tends to be paralyzing and cold i think whereas anxiety is something long-term it's always about the future it's always what's going to happen next and uh we tend to feel that as an agitation and and it warms us up it heats us up so there's quite a sort of a difference between them but for our purposes as i say uh you know fear will do

